<i>Are you worried?</i>

22
00:01:29,007 --> 00:01:31,968
DECEMBER 2007

23
00:01:31,968 --> 00:01:32,051
What did you say, Roger?

24
00:01:32,635 --> 00:01:33,761
Say it again!

25
00:01:37,223 --> 00:01:38,391
I is dead.

26
00:01:40,059 --> 00:01:42,729
Dead?! Why?

27
00:01:44,981 --> 00:01:46,733
Did Kira kill him?

28
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,443
Is that it?

29
00:01:49,235 --> 00:01:50,236
Probably...

30
00:01:50,737 --> 00:01:54,282
He said that he would get Kira
executed. . .but he was killed?!

31
00:01:54,741 --> 00:01:55,742
Is that what you're saying?!

32
00:01:56,075 --> 00:01:57,076
Mello...

33
00:02:06,711 --> 00:02:11,215
If you can't beat the game...
If you can't solve the puzzle...

34
00:02:12,425 --> 00:02:13,760
You're nothing but a loser.

35
00:02:17,639 --> 00:02:20,475
Me or Near?
So which one of us did L...?

36
00:02:23,811 --> 00:02:25,521
Neither one of you yet...

37
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:28,608
He can't choose. . .if he's dead.

38
00:02:31,861 --> 00:02:33,613
Mello... Near...

39
00:02:34,364 --> 00:02:37,325
How about the both of you
work together. . .?

40
00:02:38,034 --> 00:02:39,661
Sure. Sounds good.

41
00:02:44,457 --> 00:02:45,708
That's impossible, Roger.

42
00:02:46,793 --> 00:02:49,504
You know that Near and
I don't get along.

43
00:02:50,296 --> 00:02:51,881
We've always competed
against each other...

44
00:02:53,216 --> 00:02:54,217
Always!

45
00:03:07,563 --> 00:03:08,981
It's fine, Roger.

46
00:03:10,692 --> 00:03:12,276
Near should succeed L.

47
00:03:13,319 --> 00:03:14,904
Unlike me, Near will...

48
00:03:14,987 --> 00:03:17,699
solve this unemotionally,
like a puzzle.

49
00:03:21,994 --> 00:03:25,540
I'm going to leave this institution.

50
00:03:25,748 --> 00:03:26,791
Mello!

51
00:03:26,999 --> 00:03:29,377
I'm almost fifteen, anyway.

52
00:03:31,629 --> 00:03:33,548
I'll live my life my own way.

53
00:03:40,012 --> 00:03:43,516
A police officer who was in the vicinity
when Higuchi was arrested...

54
00:03:43,599 --> 00:03:45,601
heard that if you write

55
00:03:45,685 --> 00:03:49,981
the name of someone you know in
the notebook, that person will die.

56
00:03:50,648 --> 00:03:53,526
Are you saying that's what
the notebook of death is?

57
00:03:53,860 --> 00:03:57,488
Yes. The Japanese police
should have it right now.

58
00:03:58,740 --> 00:04:01,951
A YOUNG MAN NAMED NEAR PRESENTS
EVIDENCE ON THE KIRA CASE

59
00:04:01,993 --> 00:04:05,163
WHICH HE'S GATHERED BY HIMSELF
OVER THE LAST THREE YEARS.

60
00:04:05,413 --> 00:04:08,875
HE MEETS WITH THE PRESIDENT
ACCOMPANIED BY THE DIRECTOR OF THE FBI.

61
00:04:09,417 --> 00:04:12,628
Mr. President, the current L is one

62
00:04:12,712 --> 00:04:16,758
that the Japanese police have
created to avoid confusion.

63
00:04:16,841 --> 00:04:18,342
I is dead.

64
00:04:19,093 --> 00:04:23,598
Director Mason... Who is he?

65
00:04:24,056 --> 00:04:25,099
Well...

66
00:04:25,349 --> 00:04:29,729
He is, let’s just say...
he's L's true successor.

67
00:04:30,688 --> 00:04:32,857
THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA

68
00:04:33,024 --> 00:04:37,945
CREATES THEIR OWN INVESTIGATION TEAM
INDEPENDENT OF L TO GO AFTER KIRA.

69
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:40,198
THE SPK
(SPECIAL PROVISION FOR KIRA)

70
00:04:40,239 --> 00:04:44,452
IS COMPOSED OF HAND-PICKED
FBI AND CIA AGENTS ALONG WITH NEAR.

71
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:50,583
ABDUCTION

72
00:04:52,543 --> 00:04:53,586
But...

73
00:04:54,170 --> 00:04:56,923
It's impossible to censor
the internet and...

74
00:04:57,256 --> 00:04:59,133
the Kira case has slowed to
a dead-end lately...

75
00:04:59,926 --> 00:05:03,429
Maybe those who show people
they want killed on the internet

76
00:05:03,513 --> 00:05:05,056
should be killed.

77
00:05:06,140 --> 00:05:10,394
But Kira gets some of his information
from the internet,

78
00:05:10,478 --> 00:05:12,688
so he won't kill them.

79
00:05:13,606 --> 00:05:16,317
Matsu, your idea is full
of contradictions.

80
00:05:16,692 --> 00:05:19,529
If only people wouldn't
do bad things...

81
00:05:19,612 --> 00:05:22,740
Or rather. . .the world's become
a good place for the innocent.

82
00:05:23,533 --> 00:05:26,369
I suppose there are people
who might believe that.

83
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,205
<i>Look who's talking.</i>

84
00:05:29,622 --> 00:05:33,292
<i>No... Soon everyone will
think in that way...</i>

85
00:05:33,835 --> 00:05:36,212
Are you talking about that again?

86
00:05:36,587 --> 00:05:38,130
Please stop...

87
00:05:38,214 --> 00:05:39,882
Dear, and Light.

88
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:41,843
I'm home...

89
00:05:43,344 --> 00:05:44,637
Welcome back!

90
00:05:45,179 --> 00:05:46,305
Welcome home, Sayu.

91
00:05:46,639 --> 00:05:48,641
Light, Misa.

92
00:05:48,808 --> 00:05:52,186
It's unusual for both of
you to be here. Welcome.

93
00:05:52,562 --> 00:05:54,188
Pardon the intrusion.

94
00:05:54,814 --> 00:05:57,400
Mr. Matsuda, wasn't it?

95
00:05:57,483 --> 00:05:58,484
Oh, yes!

96
00:05:59,068 --> 00:06:00,403
It's been a while.

97
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:02,989
Thank you for taking care
of my father.

98
00:06:03,072 --> 00:06:04,699
S-Sayu...

99
00:06:05,157 --> 00:06:08,077
Y-You've grown up and
you're so pretty...

100
00:06:08,494 --> 00:06:10,496
When I last saw you,
you were like this...

101
00:06:11,539 --> 00:06:13,541
Matsu's bright red!

102
00:06:13,624 --> 00:06:15,918
Huh? No way!

103
00:06:16,002 --> 00:06:18,713
There's no way I'm letting
Sayu marry a detective.

104
00:06:18,796 --> 00:06:20,464
- Huh?
- That's right.

105
00:06:20,631 --> 00:06:22,133
I definitely don't want that.

106
00:06:22,216 --> 00:06:23,926
What? No way!

107
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:27,763
I never even got to propose...
or even confess that I love her...

108
00:06:27,847 --> 00:06:29,682
Mom and Dad.

109
00:06:29,765 --> 00:06:31,100
- Da\!

110
00:06:31,309 --> 00:06:34,103
Well... I think you're wonderful.

111
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:37,565
What. . .? R-Really, Sayu?

112
00:06:37,857 --> 00:06:41,027
Yes. I might have considered
going out with you

113
00:06:41,110 --> 00:06:43,571
if you were a little younger.

114
00:06:46,198 --> 00:06:47,783
Good one Sayu!

115
00:06:48,034 --> 00:06:51,120
Really. She's more mature
than Matsu.

116
00:06:52,204 --> 00:06:54,624
But Light,
you haven't changed one bit

117
00:06:54,707 --> 00:06:56,667
and you're as wonderful
as when I first met you.

118
00:06:57,084 --> 00:06:59,128
Light, you've already found a career...

119
00:06:59,211 --> 00:07:03,424
So stop just living together in secret
and get married already.

120
00:07:03,507 --> 00:07:05,426
That sounds good!

121
00:07:07,345 --> 00:07:09,555
<i>What an unfortunate
and heart-warming family...</i>

122
00:07:09,889 --> 00:07:10,973
<i>How fun!</i>

123
00:07:16,896 --> 00:07:17,897
What is it, Aizawa?

124
00:07:23,110 --> 00:07:24,111
Yes.

125
00:07:25,196 --> 00:07:27,156
Yes. Yes. All right.

126
00:07:28,908 --> 00:07:31,661
Matsuda, Light, come with me.

127
00:07:37,792 --> 00:07:40,461
A kidnapping?
Who was kindapped? By whom?

128
00:07:40,836 --> 00:07:43,047
Director Takimura of the NPA

129
00:07:43,464 --> 00:07:44,674
I don't know by whom.

130
00:07:45,132 --> 00:07:49,011
Damn it! As if the current situation
with the Kira case wasn't enough...

131
00:07:53,057 --> 00:07:56,310
DEPUTY DIRECTOR

132
00:07:56,811 --> 00:08:01,816
I got the phone call at 6:12.
45 minutes ago.

133
00:08:02,233 --> 00:08:05,319
We determined it was from
the director's cell phone.

134
00:08:05,903 --> 00:08:08,739
Did the kidnappers make
any demands?

135
00:08:09,365 --> 00:08:10,366
Well...

136
00:08:13,202 --> 00:08:16,914
They wanted to trade the director...
for the notebook of murder...

137
00:08:19,625 --> 00:08:21,460
<i>Who? For what purpose?</i>

138
00:08:21,961 --> 00:08:22,962
Do you suppose it's Kira?

139
00:08:23,295 --> 00:08:26,424
Well, if the existence of
the Death Note was leaked,

140
00:08:26,632 --> 00:08:28,259
countless people would want it...

141
00:08:28,509 --> 00:08:31,637
Dad, how much does
the director know?

142
00:08:32,138 --> 00:08:35,808
We tried to keep the knowledge
of the notebook within our group.

143
00:08:36,183 --> 00:08:39,979
That's right. I never discussed it
with the director.

144
00:08:41,564 --> 00:08:43,232
<i>The existence of the Death Note...</i>

145
00:08:43,816 --> 00:08:48,904
<i>Someone knows that the NPA
has it and they've come to take it...</i>

146
00:08:50,197 --> 00:08:53,909
Notify every bureau of the NPA only
about the director's kidnapping.

147
00:08:54,035 --> 00:08:55,036
Yes.

148
00:09:10,176 --> 00:09:11,510
Is it a call from the perp?

149
00:09:11,594 --> 00:09:14,972
<i>No. There's someone who wants
to meet Director Takimura.</i>

150
00:09:15,389 --> 00:09:16,432
What?

151
00:09:17,641 --> 00:09:20,728
I'm John MacEnrow,
an agent with the FBI.

152
00:09:21,270 --> 00:09:22,563
Of course, this is an alias.

153
00:09:24,106 --> 00:09:26,233
Since what I am doing concerns Kira.

154
00:09:26,358 --> 00:09:27,485
Please forgive me.

155
00:09:27,735 --> 00:09:28,819
Kira...

156
00:09:29,695 --> 00:09:32,615
The Director is out
at the moment.

157
00:09:33,032 --> 00:09:35,576
If it's all right, I'll listen to what
you have to say.

158
00:09:37,369 --> 00:09:38,579
Well, that's fine.

159
00:09:39,288 --> 00:09:41,749
Excuse me for getting
straight to the point,

160
00:09:41,832 --> 00:09:44,001
but the Japanese police
are unreliable.

161
00:09:45,628 --> 00:09:47,254
In order to solve the Kira case,

162
00:09:47,463 --> 00:09:49,590
we want you to hand over
the notebook to our country...

163
00:09:50,883 --> 00:09:52,218
So it was the FBI!

164
00:09:53,052 --> 00:09:54,637
Where have you taken
our director?!

165
00:09:54,929 --> 00:09:56,138
W-What are you talking about?

166
00:09:56,222 --> 00:09:57,223
Don't act like
you don't know!

167
00:09:57,598 --> 00:09:59,266
<i>This is a brazen criminal offense!</i>

168
00:09:59,391 --> 00:10:03,479
<i>What would we gain by hiding
the director of Japan's NPA?</i>

169
00:10:03,729 --> 00:10:05,356
<i>- Then how do you know about the notebook?!
- What's going on?</i>

170
00:10:06,398 --> 00:10:10,820
It seems that the director of the NPA
has been kidnapped by someone.

171
00:10:12,029 --> 00:10:14,240
Someone who wants
the notebook...

172
00:10:16,909 --> 00:10:18,202
Commander Rester.

173
00:10:18,369 --> 00:10:19,370
Hmm?

174
00:10:19,453 --> 00:10:23,749
Suggest to him that we'd like to help
rescue the director

175
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:25,501
and apprehend the perpetrator.

176
00:10:25,918 --> 00:10:28,212
We'll take the notebook when
we have the chance.

177
00:10:28,629 --> 00:10:29,755
All right.

178
00:10:30,256 --> 00:10:31,298
Can you hear me?

179
00:10:31,715 --> 00:10:34,301
This is headquarters.
These are your orders.

180
00:10:56,532 --> 00:10:57,950
Did he say anything?

181
00:10:58,450 --> 00:11:01,162
Seems the Japanese police
are so afraid of Kira,

182
00:11:01,328 --> 00:11:03,497
that the only ones
who are working with L are...

183
00:11:03,581 --> 00:11:07,710
Soichiro Yagami, Kanzo Mogi,
and Tota Matsuda.

184
00:11:08,335 --> 00:11:09,420
Isn't that right?

185
00:11:10,588 --> 00:11:11,630
Yeah...

186
00:11:11,964 --> 00:11:14,800
There was another called Ukita,
but he died...

187
00:11:15,426 --> 00:11:18,304
Even though you were
the director of the NPA...

188
00:11:18,387 --> 00:11:20,890
you didn't know about
the notebook?

189
00:11:22,099 --> 00:11:24,476
The Japanese police really suck.

190
00:11:26,270 --> 00:11:28,647
The highest-ranking of the three
is Yagami,

191
00:11:28,731 --> 00:11:30,900
who was the chief detective
of the task force, right?

192
00:11:31,066 --> 00:11:32,318
Yeah...

193
00:11:36,739 --> 00:11:39,575
I think there are two notebooks.

194
00:11:40,367 --> 00:11:44,038
Kira has one...
The NPA has the other.

195
00:11:46,373 --> 00:11:48,292
We'll take both.

196
00:11:49,501 --> 00:11:52,546
There's no mistake if
Mello says so.

197
00:11:53,297 --> 00:11:58,219
Has he ever been wrong since
he joined us a year and a half ago?

198
00:11:58,427 --> 00:12:04,058
But why is the guy who brought us the head
of a mafia boss Kira couldn't kill...

199
00:12:04,350 --> 00:12:06,435
so fixated on the notebook?

200
00:12:07,519 --> 00:12:09,438
I don't just want the notebook.

201
00:12:10,064 --> 00:12:11,982
I want to kill everyone
who stands in my way...

202
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:14,985
And be number one!

203
00:12:16,695 --> 00:12:19,949
<i>By whatever means necessary,
before Near does...</i>

204
00:12:57,069 --> 00:12:58,153
B-Boss!

205
00:12:58,237 --> 00:13:00,531
What is it? Be quiet.

206
00:13:00,614 --> 00:13:04,535
Sorry. Eddie and I were
just talking. . .and

207
00:13:04,743 --> 00:13:07,496
Takimura hung himself
with his necktie!

208
00:13:08,122 --> 00:13:09,164
You idiot!

209
00:13:09,581 --> 00:13:12,293
What good is a dead hostage?!

210
00:13:12,376 --> 00:13:14,253
No, that's fine.

211
00:13:15,754 --> 00:13:17,798
<i>If Kira is responsible for this...</i>

212
00:13:18,257 --> 00:13:21,885
<i>He can't touch us since he doesn't
know our names or faces.</i>

213
00:13:22,469 --> 00:13:24,972
<i>That's why he went after Takimura</i>

214
00:13:25,597 --> 00:13:26,640
<i>Which means...</i>

215
00:13:27,099 --> 00:13:30,436
<i>Kira is someone who knows
about this kidnapping...</i>

216
00:13:33,022 --> 00:13:34,189
What are we going to do, Mello?

217
00:13:35,107 --> 00:13:40,654
Kidnap Soichiro Yagami's daughter,
Sayu Yagami next.

218
00:13:45,617 --> 00:13:47,369
There are still no clues about...

219
00:13:47,453 --> 00:13:49,955
the director or the kidnappers...

220
00:13:50,205 --> 00:13:51,999
Aside from that,
why haven't they said anything

221
00:13:52,082 --> 00:13:55,210
since they kidnapped him?

222
00:13:55,669 --> 00:13:58,339
Light, there's no mistake
that the real name

223
00:13:58,422 --> 00:14:03,344
of the FBI agent who calls himself
John MacEnrow, is really Larry Conners.

224
00:14:03,552 --> 00:14:05,179
Is that so? Thank goodness.

225
00:14:05,888 --> 00:14:07,389
He's a real agent...

226
00:14:08,057 --> 00:14:11,226
The director of the FBI also said
that he would help us

227
00:14:11,310 --> 00:14:13,187
rescue director Takimura.

228
00:14:13,812 --> 00:14:15,022
I think we can trust him.

229
00:14:16,190 --> 00:14:18,650
<i>The director should
be dead by now...</i>

230
00:14:19,193 --> 00:14:20,694
<i>Why don't they say anything?</i>

231
00:14:21,653 --> 00:14:24,239
<i>Would they give up on
the deal just because he died?</i>

232
00:14:24,656 --> 00:14:26,742
<i>I didn't think we were dealing
with such weaklings...</i>

233
00:14:29,036 --> 00:14:33,123
Dad... No, everyone here
should be careful.

234
00:14:33,957 --> 00:14:35,626
The director may not know
about the notebook,

235
00:14:35,709 --> 00:14:38,462
but he knows who was
working with L.

236
00:14:38,879 --> 00:14:40,589
If that gets out, there's a chance...

237
00:14:40,672 --> 00:14:41,799
- that they'll come after us
- Light!

238
00:14:44,802 --> 00:14:47,471
I'll be a good girl tonight and
go to sleep alone, okay?

239
00:14:48,847 --> 00:14:50,224
Yeah, good night.

240
00:14:50,849 --> 00:14:51,934
Good night!

241
00:14:52,559 --> 00:14:54,478
Then I'll stay here...

242
00:14:55,813 --> 00:14:59,608
We're not the only ones in danger.
Our families and...

243
00:15:01,026 --> 00:15:02,277
The director's cell phone...

244
00:15:02,861 --> 00:15:03,904
It's from the kidnappers!

245
00:15:04,488 --> 00:15:06,615
- Aizawa!
- Yes! Tracing!

246
00:15:10,702 --> 00:15:11,703
This is Yagami.

247
00:15:12,204 --> 00:15:13,205
<i>Mr. Deputy Director?</i>

248
00:15:13,831 --> 00:15:15,624
<i>About the trade of the director
for the notebook...</i>

249
00:15:15,874 --> 00:15:16,875
<i>It's canceled.</i>

250
00:15:17,501 --> 00:15:18,710
